        "title": "feat: add clawhub scan command",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add authenticated `clawhub scan` submit/poll support for ephemeral local skill bundles and published skill scans, including JSON output and report ZIP downloads.\n- Add collision-safe scan APIs under `/api/v1/skills/-/scan`, with poll/download/batch routes backed by `skillScanRequests` and the existing ClawScan worker.\n- Move `clawhub-mod` rescans to the canonical scan endpoints and document the API/CLI/security invariants.\n\n## Verification\n- `bunx vitest run convex/httpApiV1.shared.test.ts convex/securityScan.test.ts`\n- `bun test packages/clawhub/src/cli/commands/scan.test.ts packages/clawhub-mod/src/commands/moderation.test.ts`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/schema/tsconfig.json --noEmit && bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub/tsconfig.json --noEmit && bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub-mod/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bun run lint`\n- `bun run ci:packages`\n- `bunx convex dev --once`\n- `bunx vitest run scripts/security/run-codex-scan-worker.test.ts`\n\n## Review\n- Autoreview accepted and fixed two findings: orphaned ephemeral scan uploads on invalid/pruned requests, and a `/api/v1/skills/scan` slug-route collision.\n- Final focused verification passed after moving the scan route to `/api/v1/skills/-/scan`.\n\n## Notes\n- `bun run ci:static` currently stops on an unrelated pre-existing oxfmt issue in `convex/githubAccountAgeBackfill.ts`.\n",
